-- Peru’s Imports Rose 21 Percent in January, Peru21 Reports
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2012-02-14T16:36:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/peru-s-imports-rose-21-percent-in-january-peru21-reports.html
Peru’s  imports  rose 21 percent last
month from a year earlier to $3.37 billion, Peru21  reported 
citing customs data.  Consumer goods imports rose 36 percent while purchases of
materials for the  construction industry  and machinery climbed 20
percent, the Lima-based newspaper said. Imports of raw materials
for manufacturing increased 18 percent, Peru21 said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
